p></div><div class="sc-d56bc236-6 jrySry"></div></div></a><a href="/essays/space-junk-could-have-a-transcendent-purposeful-afterlife"><div class="sc-d56bc236-9 gdveBl"><div type="essay" class="sc-82db9615-2 kVCsWP"><img alt="The International Space Station is seen at an angle through a window against the darkness of space" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 960px) 45vw, (max-width: 1440px) 30vw, 430px" srcSet="https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/18b02c5d-64c7-42a8-95be-c63a4f53559a/essay-51814546773_33e176b6e4_o.jpg?width=256&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 256w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/18b02c5d-64c7-42a8-95be-c63a4f53559a/essay-51814546773_33e176b6e4_o.jpg?width=384&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 384w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/18b02c5d-64c7-42a8-95be-c63a4f53559a/essay-51814546773_33e176b6e4_o.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 640w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/18b02c5d-64c7-42a8-95be-c63a4f53559a/essay-51814546773_33e176b6e4_o.jpg?width=750&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 750w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/18b02c5d-64c7-42a8-95be-c63a4f53559a/essay-51814546773_33e176b6e4_o.jpg?width=828&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 828w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/18b02c5d-64c7-42a8-95be-c63a4f53559a/essay-51814546773_33e176b6e4_o.jpg?width=1080&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 1080w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/18b02c5d-64c7-42a8-95be-c63a4f53559a/essay-51814546773_33e176b6e4_o.jpg?width=1200&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 1200w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/18b02c5d-64c7-42a8-95be-c63a4f53559a/essay-51814546773_33e176b6e4_o.jpg?width=1920&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 1920w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/18b02c5d-64c7-42a8-95be-c63a4f53559a/essay-51814546773_33e176b6e4_o.jpg?width=2048&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 2048w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/1